What Barry said or: http://www.joshmadison.com/software/convert/

If you do this everyday you don't need the converter... It'll come from memory.

25.4mm = 1 inch 
Metrics are all powers of 10's. Learn the scales of inch, foot, yard, mile and mm, cm, m, km, etc and you can do this with a pencil. 

